-- Greece targets 4.2 deficit next year: draft budget
-- 
-- Mon Oct 1, 2012 9:33am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/01/us-greece-economy-idUSBRE8900OZ20121001

 

 ATHENS  (Reuters) - Greece will seek to shrink its fiscal deficit to 4.2 percent of national output (GDP) next year from a projected 6.6 percent in 2012, with its economy forecast to contract by 3.8 percent, according to the country's draft budget released on Monday. 
 The draft budget targets a primary surplus of 1.1 percent of GDP next year with unemployment expected to hit 24.7 percent. Public debt is projected to reach 179.3 percenty of GDP. (Reporting by  Dina Kyriakidou )